De_terminus was my first defuse map , i did it about 2 and half year now.
For de_terminus2 i decided to completly remake that map : a new design and a new gameplay.
The map is bigger (40 spawns) , more detailled, and i hope it's more fun to play.

The action take place in a very old russian train terminus. 
The terrorists have to blown one of the two bomb sites, an industrial train for the site B , a subway station for the site A.
The CT must prevent terrorists from bombing the 2 sites. Team members must defuse any bombs that threaten those targets.

Oh no! The evil terrorists have decided to attack a dam in the middle of nowhere! Let's hope that they choose to blow up the pile of crates near an old barn instead of that multimillion pound (Oh, sorry- DOLLAR) dam that's keeping the flood waters back! The CTs start on one side of the map and must defend against the Terrorists in the usual DE manner.

This is my second bomb map that I have ever finished. I began rushing towards the end because I have plans for other maps and I just wanted to get this one out of the way, I've been adding bits to this map for over a year now. It's not the most detailed map in the world, but it's balanced and fine tuned and hopefully fun to play.

I could comment on how I could have done better with this map, and how the multiple different themes don't really go together too well, or how there isn't as much detail as I'd like there to be... but instead I'll just say that I'm pleased with this map. I start too many and I finish too few and for once I've managed to strike a balance between quantity and quality, which i can hopefully build on with future maps that I make. I have learned a lot about mapping this this map, particularly about colour schemes and gameplay. Thanks to everybody who has playtested this map at various stages in its development, especially Sonickiller, Zero and Mr13A. Thanks also to Rusty who has supported me throughout. It's nice having a motivational guru, especially one as experienced as Rusty! I have enjoyed making and playing this map and I hope that other people will too.

In case you hadn't noticed, naming maps isn't my strong point.

#### NOTE #### I updated this map to version 2 on August 24, 2010 because it was no longer playable after CS updated to Orangebox. The new versions (de_tension2 and ww_de_tension2) will now work on the new version of CS. You should delete de_tension and ww_de_tension as they can now crash CS. #### END NOTE #### The download includes two (2) maps which are variants of the same map. The namesake (de_tension2) is a standard Bomb map. The second map (ww_de_tension2) is also a standard map that has, overall, the exact same layout as the other map. The difference is that ww_de_tension2 changes depending on the number of players on the server. The intent of the changes (available paths) is to make a map that accomodates small to large crowds. ww_de_tension2 A Wall Worm map by Shawn Olson www.shawnolson.net #### THIS MAP CHANGES ! DEPENDING ON THE NUMBER OF PLAYERS * 6 Players - South tunnel opens * 12 Players - Path under bridge opens * 18 Players - Grates in water open #### Other Tips: The signs regarding the crystal caves also change depending on the number of players. This is a visual cue for the CTs to prepare for Ts coming from alternate paths.

I know this map has seen its day, but I couldn't resist. Everyone remembers the Temple from GoldenEye, right?

As my first Source map, I tried to get the overall feeling of the Temple. I know the lighting is kind of lame, and the texturing isn't perfect. But I think I brought CS:S and the Temple together well enough for a GoldenEye fan to appreciate.

There's a bombsite in the middle to keep the action focused, and the whole thing is pretty nostalgic. So give it a try, and let me know what you think.
